narratives.question_text: Were the resources provided to you by the School and University adequate for the fulfillment of the work assigned?  If not, please make suggestions.
comments: Instructor: Katherine Elizabeth Davies  Yes. Still mad that the library doesn't let us take out more than one book for more than one day. I find this very problematic.
Instructor: Katherine Elizabeth Davies  The library continues to be a nightmare.The one book policy is inconvenient and about %50 of the time they just don't know where a book is.
Instructor: Keith Krumwiede  The limited availablility of the library resources is limiting in terms of research.

Instructor: Martin Finio  Keith Krumweide, while an excellent critic, was terrible with organization. Knowing when/where class meetings are held, details of assignments, and clarity of the schedule and expectations of the course in general are very important. The lack of organization and communication detracted from the value of the studio as a whole.
Instructor: Michael Young  We need more options for post-production and support for the 3d printers.
Instructor: Michael Young  The woodshop/metalshop/allshops should have some scheduled access over the Thanksgiving break week as many students use that time to get their projects underway.
Instructor: Peter de Bretteville  The library's hours are pathetic.
Instructor: Peter de Bretteville  The resources were more than adequate.
